-- IBM earnings and revenue rise
-- 
-- Mon Jan 14, 2008 8:09am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/14/us-ibm-earnings-revenue-rise-shares-jump-idUSOSL00592420080114

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - International Business Machines Corp ( IBM.N ) said on Monday its fourth quarter earnings from continuing operations rose 24 percent to $2.80 a share, on a 10 percent increase in revenue to $28.9 billion. 

 The results, which IBM said was led by strong performances in Asia, Europe and emerging markets, pushed IBM shares up 3.4 percent to about $101 in premarket trading. Wall Street was looking for earnings before special items of $2.60 per share and revenue of $27.78 billion for the fourth quarter, according to Reuters Estimates. IBM said 6 percentage points of its revenue increase was due to currency benefit. (Reporting by  Tiffany Wu )